sequenceDiagram
    participant Exec as Execution<br/>(Server 1)
    participant Store as TaskStore
    participant Cancel as Cancel<br/>(Server 2)

    Note over Store: Task at V1 (submitted)

    Exec->>Store: CreateExecutor → load task
    Store-->>Exec: task V1

    Exec->>Store: store.Update(submitted→working, prevVersion=V1)
    Store-->>Exec: V2
    Note over Store: Task at V2 (working)

    Cancel->>Store: CreateCanceler → load task
    Store-->>Cancel: task V2

    par Execution processes events
        Exec->>Exec: agent yields artifact update
        Exec->>Store: store.Update(artifact, prevVersion=V2)
        Store-->>Exec: V3
        Note over Store: Task at V3 (working + artifact)
    and Cancelation runs
        Cancel->>Cancel: agent.Cancel yields StatusUpdate(canceled)
        Cancel->>Store: updateStatus(canceled, prevVersion=V2)
        Store-->>Cancel: ErrConcurrentModification!
        Note over Cancel: OCC retry: re-fetch task
        Cancel->>Store: store.Get(taskID)
        Store-->>Cancel: task V3 (working, not terminal)
        Cancel->>Store: updateStatus(canceled, prevVersion=V3)
        Store-->>Cancel: V4
        Note over Store: Task at V4 (canceled)
    end

    Exec->>Exec: agent yields StatusUpdate(completed)
    Exec->>Store: store.Update(completed, prevVersion=V3)
    Store-->>Exec: ErrConcurrentModification!

    Note over Exec: processor.Process catches OCC error

    Exec->>Store: store.Get(taskID)
    Store-->>Exec: task V4 (canceled = terminal)

    Note over Exec: task is terminal →<br/>return canceled task as ExecutionResult<br/>with ExecutionFailureCause = OCC error

    Exec->>Exec: execution terminates gracefully